---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { CATEGORIES, CATEGORY_KEYS } from '../consts';
---

<Base title="About" description="Who Aditya is and why this site exists.">
  <article class="post-header">
    <h1>About this place</h1>
  </article>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Hey — I'm Aditya. I work in marketing at a software security startup, I'm
      usually training for something, and I spend a lot of time thinking about how to
      live well and then talking about it to anyone who'll listen. This site is me
      writing it down instead.
    </p>
    <p>
      The whole thing is organized into four buckets — I think of them as the four
      P's:
    </p>
    <ul>
      {
        CATEGORY_KEYS.map((key) => (
          <li>
            <a href={`/${key}/`}>
              <strong>{CATEGORIES[key].name}</strong>
            </a>{' '}
            — {CATEGORIES[key].blurb}
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
    <p>
      The goal is simple: if you read this site, you'll understand me. Not the
      LinkedIn version — the actual person. Friends and family can catch up on my
      life, people I work with can see how I think, and future me can look back and
      cringe a little.
    </p>
    <p>
      If something here resonates (or you think I'm completely wrong), reach out —
      I genuinely love talking about this stuff.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
